{
  "texts": [
    "With the use of multilingual learning, they were able to demonstrate that the improvement in low-resource language where NER performance is mostly attributable to multilingual learning acting as regularization, cross-lingual sub-word characteristics and a larger named entity vocabulary.",
    "Song et al. [77] suggested a novel NER approach that takes into factor the texture of candidate entities and is based on conditional random fields (CRF).",
    "The degree of recognition granularity is character-based and word-based.",
    "Then, the authors calculate P(y|x) to achieve the best result from the input sequence, using segmented text to extract characteristics in accordance with the characteristic templates that had been taught during the training phase and also examined several recognition granularities, developed a recognition model based on CRFs and found positive outcomes with average value of recall, F-measure and accuracy is 75.09%, 78.84% and 76.91% for MEM, the average of F-measure, accuracy and recall is 82.37%,84.10% and 80.77% for CRFs and achieved recall, accuracy and F-measure is 67.01, 68.95% and 70.46% for HMM as the best of these three approaches, the CRFs achieved about 85.0%.",
    "Chopra et al. [78] presented Named Entity Recognition for Hindi language by using Hidden Markov Model (HMM)."
  ]
}